I've made this recipe twice and now it's on the top of my friend's and family's "wish list." I prefer to use either red or golden potatoes as a waxy textured potato seems to work really well.

Rating: 4
I used small red potatoes cut in small wedges. Note to self: takes longer than 45 minuts to bake - closer to 1 1/2 hours! I ended up turning heat up to 400 after the first 50 minutes. The sauce was perfect...not to overpowering to the soft potato.

Rating: 4
WOW-Yum-MmmMmm!!! Perfect with a garlic rubbed pork tenderloin. I have made this recipe twice and the second time I used baby reds with the skin on, which added some color and also garnished it with a sprinkling of fresh chopped parsley. I know this will be eaten many times in our home over the years. Happy Cooking!

