Very Good! I also used olive oil and black pepper. This was the starch compliment to the Rosemary and Garlic Lamb Chops (awesome Epicurious recipe).

Rating: 3
I agree that olive oil and black pepper are great choices for this recipe. I like to make it with baby red potatoes (using a vegetable peeler slice off a thin ring around the middle of the potato...just makes it look pretty). I usually add some chopped fresh herbs to the olive oil mixture. I've used parsley, basil, oregano and chives (separately) with great success. I also like to make it a few hours ahead of time and let the potatoes come to room temperature. It really lives up the flavors.

